{
  "texts": [
    "Using LLMs for inference incurs significant monetary costs, due to high demands of energy consumption, hardware or cloud computing time, and in terms of the environment, due to the carbon footprint of powering a number of modern tensor processing units 26, 27.",
    "Therefore, a data extraction pipeline aiming to efficiently utilize LLMs should extract the maximum amount of high-quality information and at the same time reduce the unnecessary prompting of the LLMs during the processing of millions of full-text scientific articles.",
    "Limited prior works exist on the application of LLMs for data extraction in materials science.",
    "Dagdelen et al.",
    "fine-tuned GPT-3.5 and LlaMa 2 models to extract useful records of linking dopants and host metal-organic frameworks 28."
  ]
}